        public FigureHandle getHandle​(int x,
                              int y,
                              MouseEvent e)
        Description copied from interface: DrawView
        Gets the handle (if any) that is at the mouse position. Although any information about the mouse's position is already contained in the MouseEvent e, a pair of coordinates is given to this procedure. x and y represent the constrained position of e.getX() and e.getY().
        Specified by:
        getHandle in interface DrawView
        Parameters:
        x - the constrained x-coordinate of the mouse.
        y - the constrained y-coordinate of the mouse.
        e - the mouse event
        Returns:
        the handle at the mouse position or null if no handle is selected.

      • getSelection

        public List<Figure> getSelection()
        Description copied from interface: DrawView
        Returns a list which contains the currently selected figures. The figures are ordered in the order in which they were selected by the user. If no figures are selected, then an empty list is returned. Changes applied to this list do not change the selection state of any figure. For changing the selection see methods addToSelection, removeFromSelction and clearSelection.
        Specified by:
        getSelection in interface DrawView
        Returns:
        list of selected figures
